{"contentType":"application/xhtml+xml; charset=UTF-8","body":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xmlns:dct=\"http://purl.org/dc/terms/\" xmlns:ibis=\"https://privatealpha.com/ontology/ibis/1#\" xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:skos=\"http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" xmlns:xsd=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\" prefix=\"dct: http://purl.org/dc/terms/ ibis: https://privatealpha.com/ontology/ibis/1# rdf: http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns# skos: http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core# xlink: http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink xsd: http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#\">\n  <head>\n    <title>Welcome to App::IBIS: We Have Issues.</title>\n    <base href=\"https://ibis.makethingsmakesense.com/\"/>\n    <link href=\"/asset/font-awesome.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\"/>\n    <link href=\"/asset/main.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\"/>\n    <link href=\"/feed\" rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/atom+xml\"/>\n    <script src=\"/asset/jquery.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"/>\n    <script src=\"/asset/main.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"/>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <main>\n      <section class=\"index ibis\">\n        <h1>Issue Network</h1>\n        <figure>\n          <object data=\"/ci2\" type=\"image/svg+xml\"/>\n        </figure>\n        <form accept-charset=\"utf-8\" action=\"/3de9b59b-daf9-4763-b475-d5a8713357ed\" class=\"new-ibis\" method=\"POST\">\n          <fieldset>\n            <legend>\n              <span>Start a new </span>\n              <select name=\"rdf:type :\">\n                <option value=\"ibis:Issue\">Issue</option>\n                <option value=\"ibis:Position\">Position</option>\n                <option value=\"ibis:Argument\">Argument</option>\n              </select>\n            </legend>\n            <input class=\"new-value\" name=\"= rdf:value\" type=\"text\"/>\n            <button>Go</button>\n          </fieldset>\n        </form>\n      </section>\n      <section class=\"index skos\">\n        <h1>Concept Scheme</h1>\n        <figure>\n          <object data=\"/concepts?rotate=180\" type=\"image/svg+xml\"/>\n        </figure>\n        <form accept-charset=\"utf-8\" action=\"/3de9b59b-daf9-4763-b475-d5a8713357ed\" method=\"POST\">\n          <fieldset>\n            <legend>Start a new Concept</legend>\n            <input name=\"= skos:prefLabel\" type=\"text\"/>\n            <button name=\"= rdf:type :\" value=\"skos:Concept\">Go</button>\n          </fieldset>\n        </form>\n      </section>\n      <section class=\"index list\">\n        <section>\n          <h2>Issues</h2>\n          <ul>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/7cb3bab0-1690-44f6-81ac-926e8aa34061\">It turns out people really, REALLY hate the Circos plot.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/946a42d5-4b13-478a-bc4f-2df72c730d83\">It turns out, after some use, that \"Questioned by\" is a stronger form of \"Suggests\".</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/24ff1afe-05e9-48af-90a1-62a2a12831d5\">It turns out, after some use, that Arguments are really a special kind of Issue.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/f5f307e6-010e-4afe-8006-9664a8e16f5d\">If you select a relation type in \"Create new\" and switch to \"Connect existing\" or vice versa, the relations are forgotten.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/8a886c90-7372-4b16-9499-36242dbe2911\">Two nearly-identical HTML forms on the page is unacceptable UI.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/020881cc-cd5b-4926-b4dc-f4365353d2f4\">Sometimes we want to enter new subjects, and sometimes we want to connect existing ones.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/801d61f0-2687-4617-9f7f-b792fd0502cf\">Sometimes we need to be able to disconnect the connections between two subjects that were made by accident.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/9b060070-b832-475c-8678-72380541dcd4\">It turns out Circos plots have their own problems, but they're good enough for now!</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/c34602e7-f1f2-4a22-ae15-4c7a9d231c9a\">Circos plots, being circular, create a considerable amount of wasted whitespace around them.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/5ab94eeb-fdf2-4292-8406-39a92e2aea27\">SVG+RDFa sounds like a plan. What should the graphic look like?</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/eb00d1a2-56cc-49cb-8258-e8c0e0b971aa\">Great idea. How?</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/62091b89-6204-4cdd-8901-a7fbfcdcb246\">We need to be able to be able to get a sense of the topological situation of a subject (page in context) beyond its immediate neighbourhood.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/1bfdafc5-83f0-4b5d-bab2-213aaa5bb5f5\">The number of CSS rules explodes in size when you multiply the number of classes and properties by the number of variants and states (background, hover, etc.).</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/670b5e7a-42e5-47f4-8176-54da6f51e1a9\">In the standard hexagonal HSV colour model, green is twice as bright as red, and six times as bright as blue.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d95f663f-9157-4d43-9fa9-d58d27920ebf\">We need the UI to be able to differentiate between classes of subject, as well as the different semantic relations.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/1dc8c2b2-0a9b-4974-8904-877fdbdafa64\">So we can get the data into the app, and we know what data we want to represent, but now we need an interface to navigate through it.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/f98b6cbf-dc54-4a0a-a3d7-811e071513f3\">Designing and implementing the protocol was painless enough, but what RDF vocabulary should we use to test it?</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/950d1845-2b29-44f1-a17e-a28963bc01bf\">How are we going to actually get the RDF data into storage on the server side?</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/6c5f409b-04d7-4a77-a310-b9f5cdbd4c72\">Entering ad-hoc RDF data is tedious enough when it's HTTP(S) URLs, but UUIDs make it an EXTREMELY slow-going task.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/492ba1bb-eb64-47b8-b3d7-c18a3351091e\">A big impediment to working with { RDF, Linked Data, Semantic Web } is that you have to plan your URL layout before you can begin to write down any data.</a>\n            </li>\n          </ul>\n        </section>\n        <section>\n          <h2>Positions</h2>\n          <ul>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/21c060a7-5603-4774-a240-85290019b9fc\">Use a Sugiyama-based plot.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/89de41a0-424d-4c42-8bec-ce9ddd6dfa5c\">Update the IBIS vocabulary to represent ibis:questioned-by to be a subproperty of ibis:suggests, as well as their respective inverses.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/61c244b5-2582-4792-8e8d-8562e2b0db37\">Update the IBIS vocabulary to represent ibis:Argument as a subclass of ibis:Issue. Make the appropriate changes in the app semantics.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/82914691-d9b3-4f11-87de-8eefc7892980\">Monitor changes in selected relation types in JavaScript and communicate them across forms.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/0ccddb8f-de14-4bd2-9f6c-40765af4ab16\">NOW we bring in JavaScript: toggle the visibility of one form over another with some kind of master switch.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/e12621a6-1540-4d83-8c06-e5046fe35d80\">Create two forms: one to add new elements and one to connect existing ones.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/f9c5664a-adfc-4733-bae7-0fc892879a83\">Add a \"disconnect\" button to each of the connections.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/be2c159b-451a-4a90-8fcc-c75307b63b2c\">Open up the Circos plot, mitigating the wasted space on one side.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/b4870889-2df0-4192-930b-4bf08595fdb1\">Use a Krzywinski Circos Plot.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/4ef35d7a-b8a6-4c1e-ad4d-d96ef7a7fa0d\">Use a Krzywinski Hive Plot.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/3252717c-9af9-46f5-a534-a76a88410d87\">Force-directed is always a popular.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/47682812-478a-49ca-aa4f-049302a460fe\">Render the subgraph in SVG+RDFa.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/4384a028-6eef-47d0-953a-94e624e8a48e\">Use something like D3 to visualize the subgraph.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/dc3d2df6-52e8-4c18-9724-184a7f7c93d2\">Visualize a patch in the graph (a partial spanning tree) centred around the subject.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/56bbd19a-b26e-4991-9c2f-58760e4813a0\">Use SASS to manage the complexity of the CSS.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/e6983398-a2cd-4fa3-b7b3-49c289c732b3\">Use the HSLuv colour palette to equalize the brightness across all hues.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/7c61843f-59d2-4896-8466-66214a8e2eff\">Use CSS to colour-code the different classes and properties, connecting to the embedded RDFa.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/ec95d1a9-3f88-4e28-96c3-aa6243636478\">Embed the semantic content into RDFa.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d129ee24-d1e1-46e9-aa94-a2468c93f517\">Normalize (the inverse relations) of the immediate neighbours of the subject being represented so they're all pointing the same way, link to them, and group them in lists by predicate.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/2d7e7483-ff54-4b0e-85e4-62bc2aa60914\">Have each page in the web app correspond to a subject in the semantic graph.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/52dea301-2e68-4c10-ab2d-bb0e0c95aa60\">Use the IBIS vocabulary you wrote back in 2012.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/7f9a5857-d2c0-4546-81b7-4cb0e8133ad7\">Design a simple protocol for representing RDF graph diffs in plain HTML form keys.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/18da7df0-32d4-43d6-bbed-9cfa99a6adf3\">Use JavaScript to construct RDF statement diffs and send them over with AJAX.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/ccf3bfd9-7f96-47a8-8788-e1c6f4c98d06\">Write a quick and dirty web application to abridge the process of entering RDF data.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/6d150850-636c-4ee1-be69-4dc64be920f8\">Use UUIDs (or some other easily-generated identifier) to name RDF nodes.</a>\n            </li>\n          </ul>\n        </section>\n        <section>\n          <h2>Arguments</h2>\n          <ul>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/bdc7ef94-f177-4ca6-bc3e-efcc835edd22\">Users arriving from outside the system will therefore land \"at\" a particular element.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/ee443eee-74b1-4f93-9c20-f3df54002066\">Situating the user \"at\" a given subject gives a sense of position and orientation in hypermedia space.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/9231d9b3-d758-4a02-97c5-988870725212\">Other information systems will be able to link directly to the subject.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/15edd16c-b7d7-492b-b8f6-5f35bc4ac2e2\">Krzywinski also has a design called Circos which doesn't have the aspect ratio problem.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d7789282-96d7-4120-b019-a2a43b9da6a6\">These plots are easy to implement in a few hundred lines of code.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/85067158-2473-471d-b4c7-d717c87f0279\">It turns out that hive plots are not good for dynamic data: as the contents change, their aspect ratio changes dramatically, making it impossible to wrangle them into a larger graphic design. Plus they look weird.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/e8666f1e-558a-47e3-844f-f328c1d81e25\">Force-directed graph drawing algorithms are not stable and will not produce identical (geometric) output across runs.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/57754529-268b-451a-8682-fb06ea630a68\">Force-directed (i.e. hairball) graphs get pretty hairy pretty quickly.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/43c0c321-a9f1-4930-b1e7-a2dd02bbb3e7\">That takes care of the palette problem.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d2a19834-d164-46e5-a889-1938dbcbf161\">Then we're going to have to decide how to transmit the palette to D3.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/db65c54b-d3ad-42c0-a9c7-eec71898f28d\">Then we're going to have to decide how to feed data to D3.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/9298ed47-75e0-4046-9869-b60c11a9e5e0\">We can pick up the RDFa from CSS or JavaScript and use it to further manipulate the UI.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/9fcbdf3c-da68-4cac-9826-96440489e0f3\">Writing an IBIS app will provide an opportunity to kick the tires on the vocabulary. The result might actually be useful!</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/554d2a8c-2110-4977-b6d1-0d07f8613540\">An embedding protocol is a much simpler idea; we can trot the JavaScript in later, when the app is more mature.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/610b3c51-07bd-4542-a88d-9d95b4d40bb0\">JavaScript is certainly dirty, but it isn't clear that it's quick: in particular, the extra fragility of developing client-side and server-side code at the same time.</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d134ea46-92bc-4471-97d8-468b06920724\">Using (e.g.) UUIDs for node identifiers means you can separate the problem of recording information from the problem of naming it.</a>\n            </li>\n          </ul>\n        </section>\n        <section>\n          <h2>Concepts</h2>\n          <ul>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/b95d0656-3b14-4e38-8fe2-75401ff7ee31\">Issue-Based Information System</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/fd1478d3-a6ba-430b-bdb2-2d47a4e7caf9\">JavaScript</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/7b7c4ecf-2544-4c03-ab5f-10de5e1a20d4\">Linked Data</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/86c65d14-2d23-4350-8004-233b2f3e873f\">RDF Vocabulary</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/24eb21b4-59c9-4ac5-85f8-93155e811d1f\">Resource Description Framework</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/88a93319-fb3d-492a-94f2-4288441a49a1\">Semantic Web</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/d2189a63-4313-490b-98de-190e9fd947f8\">Uniform Resource Identifier</a>\n            </li>\n            <li>\n              <a href=\"/27a05aeb-017c-484d-b490-c6949e6eacbc\">Universally Unique Identifier</a>\n            </li>\n          </ul>\n        </section>\n      </section>\n    </main>\n    <footer>\n      <nav>\n        <ul>\n          <li>\n            <a href=\"/\">Â </a>\n          </li>\n          <li>\n            <a href=\"/we-have-issues\">What is this thing?</a>\n          </li>\n        </ul>\n      </nav>\n    </footer>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"}